  , issueCommentBody =
      "This is the syntax in the various drivers, where `conn` is a connection object in each case. In all cases except Java, the `clientPort` is an integer and `clientAddress` is a string.\r\n\r\nJavaScript\r\n```js\r\n// Note: These are properties of the connection, not methods\r\nconn.clientPort\r\nconn.clientAddress\r\n```\r\n\r\nPython\r\n```py\r\nconn.client_port()\r\nconn.client_address()\r\n```\r\n\r\nRuby\r\n```ruby\r\n# These are methods, you can optionally use `()`\r\nconn.client_port\r\nconn.client_address\r\n```\r\n\r\nJava\r\n```java\r\nconn.clientPort() // Returns Optional<Integer>\r\nconn.clientAddress() // Returns Optional<SocketAddress>\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe client port is the outgoing TCP port that the connection uses on the client-side. It is randomly assigned by the operating system, and can be used to match client entries in the `r.db('rethinkdb').table('jobs')` table to a client process."
